description: From earlier ingrave, equivalent to en- +‎ grave (“to carve, engrave”). More at grave.

verbs.description: engrave (third-person singular simple present engraves, present participle engraving, simple past and past participle engraved)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To carve text or symbols into (something), usually for the purposes of identification or art.
examples: He engraved the plaque with his name.

verbs.description: engrave (third-person singular simple present engraves, present participle engraving, simple past and past participle engraved)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To put in a grave, to bury.
